          <num>352-18</num>
          <heading>Establishment of trust accounts</heading>
          <content>
            <p>§352-18  Establishment of trust accounts.
All sums collected pursuant to sections 352
-
16 and 352
-
17, and
from other authorized sources shall be placed in a bank trust account or
federally insured savings account to the credit of persons committed pursuant
to this chapter.  The director or director's agent shall maintain individual
ledger accounts for each committed person and shall issue each person a
periodic statement showing deposits and withdrawals. [L 1980, c 303, pt of
§8(1)]
